Description. Growth Form. Massive ficiform or egg cup shaped sponge with a shallow apical dish, a short broad based stem and an uneven margin ( Figs 1 , 2 ); outer surface bearing numerous, short (up to 1 cm ), unevenly distributed wart like buds (
Fig. 3
). Dimensions are 3–7.5 cm long, 2.5–7 cm wide and 3–5 cm high. Several specimens have a roughly circular base which is approximately 1 cm less in diameter than the body.

Choanosomal skeleton . The choanosomal skeleton consists of a 3 D matrix of regular and slightly curved dicranoclone desmas. These desmas form a distinct root/vine like mesh (as described in
Schlacher-Hoenlinger et al. 2005
). Choanosomal microscleres consist of microspinose spiraster streptasters with slender arms. There are bundles of smooth very long oxeas in long thick brushes piercing the surface.
